            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EPrayer%20is%20the%20mightiest%20force%20upon%20earth.%20It%20is%20powerful%20enough%20to%20help%20the%20troubled%2C%20the%20sick%2C%20or%20the%20sinner%20(James%205%3A13-16).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EElijah%20is%20an%20example%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20%22pray-ers%22%20in%20the%20Bible.%20He%20was%20subject%20to%20the%20same%20human%20frailties%20that%20we%20experience%20when%20we%20pray%3A%20boredom%2C%20fatigue%2C%20discouragement%2C%20hunger%2C%20and%20thirst.%20However%2C%20so%20powerful%20a%20prayer%20warrior%20was%20he%20that%20when%20he%20prayed%20for%20no%20rain%2C%20%22none%20fell%20for%20the%20next%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years!%22%20(James%205%3A17).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EElijah%20was%20consistent%20for%20more%20than%20three%20years%20in%20holding%20back%20the%20rain%20through%20prayer.%20Then%2C%20during%20a%20seven-part%20prayer%20drama%20on%20Mount%20Carmel%2C%20he%20sent%20his%20servant%20to%20look%20for%20a%20cloud%20of%20rain%20over%20the%20Mediterranean.%20Six%20times%20the%20servant%20returned%20discouraged.%20Finally%2C%20Elijah's%20prayer%20broke%20through%2C%20and%20the%20cloud%20of%20rain%20soaked%20the%20parched%20soil.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOur%20prayer%20goal%3F%20More%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20we%20must%20pray%20for%20those%20who%20have%20strayed%20from%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20Gospel%20and%20work%20to%20bring%20them%20back%20to%20right%20relationship%20with%20God%20(vv.%2019-20).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPray%20on%2C%20fervent%20Christian.%20The%20cloud%20of%20salvation%20is%20beginning%20to%20rise!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
